German Majority Approves of Merkel’s Crisis Handling, FOCUS Says

-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 
2011-08-28T12:46:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/german-majority-approves-of-merkel-s-crisis-handling-focus-says.html
A majority of Germans approve of the
way German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  has represented  Germany ’s
interests in the financial crisis,  Focus  magazine reported,
citing a poll by  Emnid .  Merkel is doing “very well” or “rather well,” 53
percent of the respondents said, while 44 percent said she
wasn’t doing well, according to Focus.  To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt at   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
